FT  09 SEP 93 / Two killed as Haiti mayor returns for reinstatement
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TWO people were killed and several wounded when a ceremony to return the
capital's pro-democracy mayor to his post sparked shooting and other
violence yesterday, independent radio stations said, Reuter reports from
Port-au-Prince.
There was no immediate confirmation of the reports.
Six days ago a new government took over with the aim of bringing exiled
President Jean-Bertrand Aristide back to power next month.
Scores of City Hall employees opposed to President Aristide used rocks and
staves to attack departing cars crammed with government ministers and
foreign diplomats at the end of a ceremony formally reinstating Mayor Evans
Paul.
