<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 93 / Survey of Software at Work - Autumn 1993 (2): Record entries
for software competition - Business Software Challenge '90s
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
   THIS YEAR'S competition for young software writers
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
'Business Software Challenge 90s' - has attracted a record number of
entries.
Prizes to the value of Pounds 20,000, plus a range of hardware and software,
are to be offered to the winners who will be announced in the next issue of
the FT's Software At Work, in November.
The competition is sponsored and funded by the software vendor, Computer
Associates, which founded the event two years ago as a way to encourage
students in the UK to write applications for solving real business problems.
The competition is aimed at students and recent graduates in higher
education, working individually or in teams. Winners in previous years have
been responsible for a number of highly promising products - and some have
gone on to full-time careers in software design.
Although entries for this year closed on August 27, general details about
the competition are available from:
The Competition Secretary,
Business Software Challenge 90s
