FT  08 SEP 93 / International Company News: Casino group seeks ADollars 246m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MELBOURNE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AN Australian company that successfully bid for a licence to build and
operate a casino in Melbourne aims to raise ADollars 246m (USDollars
164.00m) through an initial public offering of shares, AP-DJ reports from
Melbourne.
The licence was awarded to a consortium of companies, including Foster's
Brewing and property developer Hudson Conway, following a bid earlier this
week of ADollars 750m to the Victoria state government.
The consortium has formed Crown Casino which is to take a stock market
listing late this year or early 1994 to pay for part of their successful
bid.
Investment institutions and private shareholders will be offered ADollars
246.0m of shares, or 60 per cent of Crown, and the three-member consortium
will take up the rest, giving the company an issued capital of ADollars
410m.
