continuing to win new contracts in the Middle East and Far East. In
addition, the proposed joint venture in China was expected to establish an
entry into the market.
Earnings per share rose by 7 per cent to 9.76p (9.1p) after allowing for the
joint venture dilution, and the recommended final dividend of 3.07p makes a
total for the year of 4.4p (special 0.3p).
The 1992 flotation proceeds helped reduce interest charges to Pounds 692,000
(Pounds 1.44m) in the year. Gearing at year end was 37 per cent.
