<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 93 / RSI an epidemic, says GMB chief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN is suffering an epidemic of repetitive strain injury (RSI), which
afflicts more than 100,000 people, said Mr Dick Pickering, president of the
GMB general union.
Mr Pickering, launching a TUC campaign on RSI, said that compensation claims
could cost employers Pounds 500m, and that 500,000 working days a year are
lost.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P9431 Administration of Public Health Programs.
</IN>
<XX>
